---
import StarlightPage from "@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro";
import { CardGrid, Card, LinkButton } from "@astrojs/starlight/components";
---

<style>
  .section {
    padding: 4rem 1rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, transparent, #ccc 30%, #ccc 70%, transparent);
    background-position: 0 100%;
    background-size: 100% 2px;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section p {
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    list-style-type: disc;
  }

  ul li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>

<StarlightPage frontmatter={{
  title: "Home",
  template: "splash",
  hero: {
    title: "Geometry Dash: Surge",
    image: {
      file: {
        src: "logo.png",
        width: 336,
        height: 336,
        format: "png"
      }
    },
    actions: [
      { text: "Learn More", link: "#features", icon: "down-arrow" },
      { text: "Install", link: "/install", icon: "right-arrow" }
    ]
  }
}}>

<section id="about" class="section">
  <h2>What is GD: Surge?</h2>
  <p><strong>Geometry Dash: Surge</strong> is a Geometry Dash fangame built with Geode. It includes new main levels, a new shop, and TONS of lore...</p>
</section>

<section id="features" class="section">
  <h2>Features</h2>
  <CardGrid>
    <Card title="Classic Levels">
      Six original-style levels inspired by the Geometry Dash legacy, crafted with custom visuals and tweaks.
    </Card>
    <Card title="Platformer Mode">
      Side-scrolling action with five unique levels (and five more planned). Platforming meets rhythm.
    </Card>
    <Card title="Vault Codes">
      Discover hidden codes throughout the game. Think deeper, search harderâ€”what will you unlock?
    </Card>
    <Card title="Da Shop">
      A new shop with exclusive, new items.
    </Card>
  </CardGrid>
</section>

<section id="roadmap" class="section">
  <h2>Development Roadmap</h2>
  <p>The project is active and evolving. Expect new levels, polish updates, and community-driven features. If you're curious about what's next, check out the full roadmap:</p>
  <LinkButton href="https://www.notion.so/omgrod/Geometry-Dash-Surge-1f3e014e65e38004a013d4329ac255d6?pvs=4" icon="right-arrow">View Roadmap</LinkButton>
</section>

<section id="incompatibilities" class="section">
  <h2>Compatibility</h2>
  <p>To avoid save corruption or conflicts, take note of the following:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GDPS Switcher:</strong> Will reset save data each time you switch versions.</li>
    <li><strong>Other Fangame Mods:</strong> Not compatible if installed in the same directory.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section id="credits" class="section">
  <h2>Credits</h2>
  <CardGrid>
    <Card title="Development Team">
      <ul>
        <li>OmgRod (Lead Developer)</li>
        <li>MobMasterMind (Icons)</li>
        <li>BitZ (GD World Code)</li>
        <li>Capeling (Other fangame code)</li>
        <li>Alphalaneous (Logo Design)</li>
        <li>Jasmine (Bindings)</li>
      </ul>
    </Card>
    <Card title="Level Creators">
      <ul>
        <li>OmgRod</li>
        <li>Flingus</li>
        <li>MobMasterMind</li>
      </ul>
    </Card>
    <Card title="Music">
      <ul>
        <li>Boom Kitty - Badland, Tomb, Detour</li>
        <li>Waterflame - Unstable Geometry</li>
        <li>dj-Nate - The Beginning of Time, Thermodynamix</li>
      </ul>
    </Card>
  </CardGrid>
</section>

<section id="feedback" class="section">
  <h2>Found a Bug?</h2>
  <p>Surge is open to community input. If you discover an issue or want to suggest a feature, open a ticket on our GitHub issue tracker.</p>
  <LinkButton href="https://github.com/OmgRod/GD-Surge/issues" icon="pencil">Submit Feedback</LinkButton>
</section>

</StarlightPage>
